Introduction

Lee Jihoon, better known by his stage name Woozi, is a South Korean singer, dancer, songwriter, composer, arranger, and producer under Pledis Entertainment. He is the main dancer, lead vocalist, and sub-rapper of the boy group SEVENTEEN. On January 3, 2022, Woozi released his first mixtape, titled Ruby.

Within the group, Woozi is the leader of SVT VOCAL Team and is responsible for producing most of their songs. He has also taken part in writing songs for other artists, such as Ailee and Eric Nam. Woozi is also credited with writing "Downpour," which happens to be the last digital single of the project girl group I.O.I.
